These are changes for 4.0.0 release, compared to 3.11.0.
Already done:
- Updated to 26.1.1
- Remapped to Mojmap
- Changed package from dev.emi.trinkets to eu.pb4.trinkets
- Renamed TrinketItem, you should use tags, component and TrinketCallback instead.
- Renamed Trinket to TrinketCallback
- Methods to get/set the Trinket(Callback) were moved from TrinketsAPI to TrinketCallback.
- Moved non-api classes to .impl package
- TrinketEnums.DropRule -> TrinketDropRule
- TrinketComponent -> TrinketAttachment
- New trinket equipment predicates:
  - trinkets:default -> allows the component and the tag to define the slot item is allowed in.
  - trinket:component -> allows the component to define the slot item is allowed in.
- Changed default predicates from `trinket:tag` to `trinkets:default`
- SlotAttributes was reworked and no longer depends on unregistered attribute instances:
  - Instead it provides a method that will register / retrieve an attribute to use statically.
- Reworked slot icons to work more like vanilla:
  - Icons no longer have a background.
  - Moved icon files from 'namespace:textures/gui/slots' to 'namespace:textures/gui/sprites/container/slots'
  - Ids however should change from 'namespace:gui/slots' to 'namespace:container/slots'
- Slot count is only calculated on server and sent from it.
- Events now use the Yumi Framework over Fabric one (as pre-requisite of neoforge support)
- Predicates can now work as an AND and OR logic in json, by using objects with "and" key or "or" key. These can be nested as much as one needs.
- Dropped dependency on Cardinal Components API.
- Added support for NeoForge Mod Loader
- minecraft:piglin_safe_armor tag now works on trinkets.
- Glider component now works correctly in trinkets slots (no visual change for things like wings yet!).
- Fixed tags in trinkets entity slot definition.
- A bunch of logic fixes for slot resizing and item removal.
- Trinkets now has a config file (no ui yet), to toggle some features:
  - Extra slot indicator (disabled by default).
- Slot name now displays even if callback prevents equipment.
  - It will however change the color from blue to dark gray.
- Data Driven Trinket Rendering in addition to improved compatibility for code-driven one:
  - https://github.com/Patbox/trinkets/wiki/Data-Driven-Trinket-rendering-asset-definition.

Planned:
- General implementation cleanup
